WEBVTT

00:04.500 --> 00:07.648
<i>♪ We are the Crystal Gems ♪</i>

00:07.749 --> 00:10.270
<i>♪ we'll always save the day ♪</i>

00:10.331 --> 00:12.403
<i>♪ and if you think we can't ♪</i>

00:12.405 --> 00:15.272
<i>♪ we'll always find a way ♪</i>

00:15.274 --> 00:19.176
<i>- # that's why the people #
- # of this world #</i>

00:19.178 --> 00:21.545
<i>- # believe in... #
- # Garnet #</i>

00:21.547 --> 00:24.348
<i>- # Amethyst #
- # and Pearl #</i>

00:24.350 --> 00:26.017
<i>♪ And Steven! ♪</i>

00:26.181 --> 00:27.874
<b>1x39 - "Future Vision" </b>

00:27.878 --> 00:29.747
<i><font color=#ca> ~ Fora Temer ~ </font></i>

00:31.188 --> 00:34.924
Okay, everyone. I think
we all know what's going on here.

00:34.925 --> 00:39.448
I'm sure you knew this day
was coming sooner or later.

00:39.849 --> 00:44.366
I understand your concern, but
that language was inappropriate.

00:44.367 --> 00:47.076
I'm a Crystal Gem.
I'm a big boy now.

00:47.077 --> 00:51.568
And I got to stop saying stuff like,
"I'm a big boy now."

00:52.569 --> 00:58.614
Look, I'm sure this is tough, but
let's all be positive about this.

00:58.682 --> 01:03.018
Man, I guess I can't be in
the Ninja Squad anymore.

01:03.086 --> 01:07.040
Get out of my life, Ninja Squad!

01:07.041 --> 01:09.758
Yeah! New Ninja Squad!

01:09.826 --> 01:13.429
Mm. That's everything for now.
Hmm?

01:13.497 --> 01:16.799
Oh.
Master of ceremonies bear bear.

01:16.867 --> 01:20.703
I guess I should get rid of you, too?

01:20.770 --> 01:22.571
Nah.
You never know when I'll need

01:22.672 --> 01:25.938
a cool deejay for a fun party, right?

01:26.224 --> 01:29.440
Who-o-o-o-ah!

01:29.441 --> 01:33.157
- Uh. Garnet!
- Good morning to you, Steven.

01:33.158 --> 01:37.012
Boy, I sure am lucky
you showed up when you did.

01:37.013 --> 01:40.156
- Luck's got nothing to do with it.
- Wait.

01:40.223 --> 01:43.425
- What do you mean by that?
- Don't worry about it.

01:43.493 --> 01:46.028
No, seriously.
How do you always know

01:46.096 --> 01:47.696
- where to be?
- Mmm.

01:47.764 --> 01:50.699
I don't think you can handle
that information.

01:50.767 --> 01:55.437
Are you gonna tell me
something cool about yourself?

01:55.505 --> 01:57.806
- Nope.
- Aw, come on.

01:57.874 --> 02:03.379
- I'm a ... large... man now.
- Well...

02:03.446 --> 02:08.517
I guess you could say that
I have a sort of... future vision.

02:08.618 --> 02:13.063
I'm able to see possible
outcomes to most situations,

02:13.064 --> 02:17.151
which comes in handy since you
seem to attract a lot of danger.

02:17.152 --> 02:21.764
- Well, danger is my middle name.
- That's a lie.

02:21.831 --> 02:25.701
Your middle name is cutie pie.

02:31.924 --> 02:35.110
<i>Oon-dohng hah jah!
Cha!</i>

02:35.212 --> 02:38.557
<i>Hana dool, dool dool.</i>

02:38.558 --> 02:41.483
<i>Seht dool, neht dool.</i>

02:41.585 --> 02:44.420
<i>Duh-suht dool.
Yuh-suht dool.</i>

02:44.521 --> 02:47.790
<i>Il-gohb dool, yuh-duhlp.
Geh sohk hah jah!</i>

02:47.857 --> 02:50.651
<i>Hana dool, dool dool.</i>

02:50.652 --> 02:53.095
<i>Seht dool, neht dool.</i>

02:53.163 --> 02:56.031
<i>Duh-suht dool.
Yuh-suht dool.</i>

02:56.099 --> 02:58.567
<i>Il-gohb dool.
Yuh-duhlp ... </i>

02:58.635 --> 03:01.136
Okay, we're done.

03:01.204 --> 03:03.906
But the day still has
so much potential.

03:04.007 --> 03:06.609
Garnet, what are my breakfast
possibilities?

03:06.676 --> 03:09.078
Well, you're already
outside, so you'll probably

03:09.145 --> 03:14.357
- go to the Big Donut.
- Wow. That's amazing.

03:14.358 --> 03:18.410
Um, do you see any
possible futures where

03:18.411 --> 03:22.558
you, um, come with me
and have a great time?

03:22.626 --> 03:23.800
Hmm.

03:25.000 --> 03:31.074
Advertise your product or brand here
